SOUTHERN NEVADA
ZOOLOGICAL - BOTANICAL PARK
The Southern Nevada
Zoological - Botanical Park , informally known as the Las Vegas Zoo , was a , nonprofit Zoological park and botanical garden located in Las Vegas , Nevada that closed in September 2013 .
It was located northwest of the Las Vegas Strip , about 15 minutes away .
It focused primarily on the education of desert life and habitat protection .
Its mission statement was to " educate and entertain the public by displaying a variety of plants and animals " .
An admission fee was charged .
The park included a small gem exhibit area and a small gift shop at the main exit .
The gift shop and admission fees helped support the zoo .
EXHIBITS
Section::::Exhibits .
The zoological park exhibited over 150 species of plants and animals , including the last family of Barbary apes in the United States .
